      "Press leaves briefly before printing (optional): place between paper towels under a heavy book for 30-60 minutes. Flat leaves produce cleaner prints than curled ones.",
      "Prepare the workspace: lay scrap paper on the table before placing the leaf. This catches paint and keeps the work area clean.",
      "Lay a leaf vein-side up on scrap paper: the veins are on the underside of most leaves. The raised vein structure creates the beautiful texture in the print.",
      "Paint the leaf surface with a thin, even layer of paint: use a small roller for the most even coverage, or a flat brush. Load generously but not drippingly. Too little paint = faint print; too much = blobs.",
      "Press the painted leaf firmly onto the card: place it paint-side down and press firmly across the entire surface with the palm of your hand. Press to the edges and tips.",
      "Peel back in one smooth movement to reveal the print: lift one corner and peel back smoothly. Replacing it after peeking creates a ghost double-print.",
