      "Add simple details with a fine marker: a ground line, a stem below the leaf, a simple sky, or small insects on the leaf surface. These 2-minute additions make the card look considered and complete.",
      "Create matching sets: re-ink the same leaf and print 6 identical copies. A matching set of cards makes a cohesive gift or a complete seasonal greeting set.",
      "Write a message inside: a handwritten card with a hand-printed cover is genuinely superior to any commercially produced card. The combination of art and personal message is irreplaceable.",
      "Experiment with other objects as printing tools: cut celery (prints like a flower), halved capsicum, citrus fruit halves, or corn on the cob. Each produces a completely different and surprising pattern."
