      "Strain out the cabbage pieces: the remaining deep purple liquid is your pH indicator. Let it cool before children handle it.",
      "Set up the experiment: pour about 20ml of cabbage indicator into each small cup or test tube. Label each cup with the test substance name. This is the control colour - note it.",
      "Add each test substance to its own cup: use a consistent small amount (1 teaspoon) for each. Use separate spoons to avoid cross-contamination.",
      "Ask children to predict before each addition: what colour do they think it will turn? Record predictions.",
      "Observe and record the colour changes: pink and red indicate acid; purple indicates neutral; blue-green indicates mildly alkaline; bright green or yellow indicates strongly alkaline.",
