    "category": "seasonal",
    "emoji": "🐣",
    "ages": "3-10",
    "time": "20 min",
    "difficulty": "easy",
    "supplies": [
      "200g milk chocolate",
      "75g shredded wheat or cornflakes",
      "Mini chocolate eggs",
      "Cupcake cases",
      "A bowl and saucepan for melting"
    ],
    "description": "Melt chocolate, mix with shredded wheat to make nests, then fill with mini eggs - no baking required.",
    "steps": [
      "Introduce the recipe: Easter Egg Nest Cakes are a no-bake chocolate treat made by mixing melted chocolate with shredded wheat to form a nest shape, then filling with mini chocolate eggs. They are one of the few Easter foods children can make almost entirely independently.",
      "Gather ingredients: 200g milk chocolate, 75g shredded wheat (or cornflakes for a crunchier result), mini chocolate eggs (3 per nest), and cupcake cases.",
      "Set up a double boiler: fill a saucepan with about 5cm of water and bring to a gentle simmer. Place a heatproof bowl on top, making sure it does not touch the water. This method melts chocolate gently without burning.",
      "Melt the chocolate: break the chocolate into small pieces and place in the bowl. Stir constantly as it melts. The chocolate is ready when it is completely smooth with no lumps.",
      "Remove from heat: lift the bowl off the saucepan carefully using oven mitts - the bowl will be hot. Place on a heatproof surface.",
      "Break and mix the shredded wheat: break the shredded wheat into small irregular pieces over the melted chocolate bowl. Stir thoroughly until every piece is fully coated. Work quickly as the chocolate begins setting.",
      "Prepare the cases: place cupcake cases on a baking tray or plate. Have the mini eggs ready to hand.",
      "Shape the nests: spoon the chocolate mixture into each cupcake case. Fill generously. Use the back of the spoon to press down in the centre and build up the sides slightly, creating a nest hollow.",
      "Add the eggs: while the chocolate is still soft, press 3 mini eggs into the hollow of each nest. They should sit visibly on top and stay in place as the chocolate sets.",
      "Refrigerate: place the tray in the fridge for at least 30 minutes until the chocolate is completely set and the nests are firm.",
      "Test for doneness: the nests should be solid and hold their shape when lifted from the cases. If still soft, return to the fridge for another 15 minutes.",
      "Serve and store: keep in the fridge until ready to serve. They hold well for 3-4 days refrigerated and make excellent gifts in a decorated box."
    ],
    "tips": "Cornflakes work just as well as shredded wheat and give a crunchier texture. These are a guaranteed crowd-pleaser and children can make them almost entirely independently."
